## **File Structure Overview**

```
extensions/irc/
├── openclaw.plugin.json          # Plugin manifest
├── package.json                  # NPM package metadata
├── index.ts                      # Main entry point (exports)
├── api.ts                        # API barrel (public exports)
├── runtime-api.ts                # Runtime API barrel (private)
├── setup-entry.ts                # Setup plugin entry
├── channel-config-api.ts         # Channel config API barrel
├── src/
│   ├── channel.ts                # Main ChannelPlugin implementation
│   ├── types.ts                  # Type definitions
│   ├── runtime.ts                # Runtime store creation
│   ├── accounts.ts               # Account resolution logic
│   ├── setup-core.ts             # Core setup adapter functions
│   ├── setup-surface.ts          # Setup wizard UI flows
│   ├── config-schema.ts          # Zod validation schemas
│   ├── config-ui-hints.ts        # UI hints for config display
│   ├── normalize.ts              # IRC message/allowlist normalization
│   ├── monitor.ts                # Main connection monitor loop
│   ├── client.ts                 # IRC protocol client (TLS/non-TLS)
│   ├── connect-options.ts        # Connect options builder
│   ├── inbound.ts                # Inbound message handler
│   ├── send.ts                   # Outbound message sender
│   ├── protocol.ts               # IRC protocol parsing/formatting
│   ├── control-chars.ts          # IRC control character handling
│   ├── probe.ts                  # Connection probe/health check
│   ├── policy.ts                 # Group & mention policy resolvers
│   └── [test files]              # Comprehensive test coverage
└── src/
```

---

## **Key Configuration Files**

### **openclaw.plugin.json** (Plugin Manifest)

```json
{
  "id": "irc",
  "channels": ["irc"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

This is the minimal manifest. Key points:
- `id`: Unique plugin identifier
- `channels`: Array of channel types this plugin provides
- `configSchema`: JSON Schema for top-level plugin config (usually empty for channel plugins)

### **package.json** (NPM Metadata)

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/irc",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw IRC channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "irc",
      "label": "IRC",
      "selectionLabel": "IRC (Server + Nick)",
      "detailLabel": "IRC",
      "docsPath": "/channels/irc",
      "docsLabel": "irc",
      "blurb": "classic IRC networks with DM/channel routing and pairing controls.",
      "aliases": ["internet-relay-chat"],
      "systemImage": "network"
    }
  }
}
```

Critical `openclaw` fields:
- `extensions`: Entry points for the plugin
- `setupEntry`: Setup wizard entry point
- `channel`: Channel metadata (label, docs link, UI icons)

---

## **Main Entry Points**

### **index.ts** (Plugin Export)

```typescript
import type { ChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { ircPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
import { setIrcRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export { ircPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
export { setIrcRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export default defineChannelPluginEntry({
  id: "irc",
  name: "IRC",
  description: "IRC channel plugin",
  plugin: ircPlugin as ChannelPlugin,
  setRuntime: setIrcRuntime,
});
```

Key pattern:
- `defineChannelPluginEntry` wraps the plugin and runtime setter
- Exports the actual plugin for testing
- Sets up integration with the OpenClaw system

### **setup-entry.ts** (Setup Wizard Entry)

```typescript
import { defineSetupPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { ircPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";

export default defineSetupPluginEntry(ircPlugin);
```

Simple wrapper that integrates the plugin with the setup system.

### **api.ts** (Public API Barrel)

```typescript
export * from "./src/accounts.js";
export * from "./src/setup-surface.js";
```

Exports public APIs for external use (accounts, setup UI).

### **runtime-api.ts** (Private Runtime Barrel)

```typescript
// Re-exports from plugin SDK with channel-specific types
export {
  buildBaseChannelStatusSummary,
  createAccountStatusSink,
  chunkTextForOutbound,
  // ... more exports
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc";
export type {
  ChannelPlugin,
  DmPolicy,
  GroupPolicy,
  // ... more types
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc";
```

Internal barrel for the IRC plugin's runtime dependencies.

---

## **Core Type Definitions** (src/types.ts)

```typescript
// Account configuration (per IRC server/account)
export type IrcAccountConfig = {
  name?: string;
  enabled?: boolean;
  host?: string;
  port?: number;
  tls?: boolean;
  nick?: string;
  username?: string;
  realname?: string;
  password?: string;
  passwordFile?: string;
  nickserv?: IrcNickServConfig;
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  defaultTo?: string;
  groupPolicy?: GroupPolicy;
  groupAllowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  groups?: Record<string, IrcChannelConfig>;
  channels?: string[];
  markdown?: MarkdownConfig;
  historyLimit?: number;
  dmHistoryLimit?: number;
  dms?: Record<string, DmConfig>;
  textChunkLimit?: number;
  chunkMode?: "length" | "newline";
  blockStreaming?: boolean;
  blockStreamingCoalesce?: BlockStreamingCoalesceConfig;
  responsePrefix?: string;
  mediaMaxMb?: number;
};

// Per-channel configuration
export type IrcChannelConfig = {
  requireMention?: boolean;
  tools?: GroupToolPolicyConfig;
  toolsBySender?: GroupToolPolicyBySenderConfig;
  skills?: string[];
  enabled?: boolean;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  systemPrompt?: string;
};

// NickServ configuration
export type IrcNickServConfig = {
  enabled?: boolean;
  service?: string;
  password?: string;
  passwordFile?: string;
  register?: boolean;
  registerEmail?: string;
};

// Top-level IRC config
export type IrcConfig = IrcAccountConfig & {
  accounts?: Record<string, IrcAccountConfig>;
  defaultAccount?: string;
};

// Inbound message structure
export type IrcInboundMessage = {
  messageId: string;
  target: string; // channel name for groups, sender nick for DMs
  rawTarget?: string; // raw IRC PRIVMSG target
  senderNick: string;
  senderUser?: string;
  senderHost?: string;
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
  isGroup: boolean;
};

// Probe result (health check)
export type IrcProbe = BaseProbeResult<string> & {
  host: string;
  port: number;
  tls: boolean;
  nick: string;
  latencyMs?: number;
};
```

---

## **Account Resolution** (src/accounts.ts)

```typescript
export type ResolvedIrcAccount = {
  accountId: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  name?: string;
  configured: boolean; // true if host && nick present
  host: string;
  port: number;
  tls: boolean;
  nick: string;
  username: string;
  realname: string;
  password: string;
  passwordSource: "env" | "passwordFile" | "config" | "none";
  config: IrcAccountConfig;
};

// Main function: resolves account with env var fallbacks
export function resolveIrcAccount(params: {
  cfg: CoreConfig;
  accountId?: string | null;
}): ResolvedIrcAccount

// Lists all configured IRC account IDs
export function listIrcAccountIds(cfg: CoreConfig): string[]

// Gets the default account ID (e.g., "default")
export function resolveDefaultIrcAccountId(cfg: CoreConfig): string
```

**Password Resolution Priority**:
1. Environment variable (`IRC_PASSWORD` for default account)
2. Password file (`channels.irc.passwordFile`)
3. Config value (`channels.irc.password`)
4. Empty string if none found

**NickServ Password** follows similar fallback pattern with `IRC_NICKSERV_PASSWORD` env var.

---

## **Configuration Schema** (src/config-schema.ts)

Uses Zod for runtime validation:

```typescript
export const IrcAccountSchemaBase = z.object({
  name: z.string().optional(),
  enabled: z.boolean().optional(),
  host: z.string().optional(),
  port: z.number().int().min(1).max(65535).optional(),
  tls: z.boolean().optional(),
  nick: z.string().optional(),
  username: z.string().optional(),
  realname: z.string().optional(),
  password: z.string().optional(),
  passwordFile: z.string().optional(),
  nickserv: IrcNickServSchema.optional(),
